# Generic Log Handler – Architecture & Technology

## Layered Architecture (C#/.NET 10)

| Project | Responsibility |
|---------|----------------|
| **GenericLogHandler.Core** | Interfaces, models, configuration DTOs. No dependencies on Data/Web. |
| **GenericLogHandler.Data** | EF Core `LoggingDbContext`, `LogRepository`. Depends only on Core. |
| **GenericLogHandler.ImportService** | Background import service + Alert Agent. Creates importers per source type. |
| **GenericLogHandler.WebApi** | REST API + static web UI from `wwwroot`. DedgeAuth SSO, OpenAPI + Scalar, Serilog. |

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Runtime | .NET 10 |
| API | ASP.NET Core 10, REST, OpenAPI (Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi + Scalar.AspNetCore) |
| ORM | Entity Framework Core 10.x |
| Database | PostgreSQL (primary), DB2/SQL Server supported |
| Logging | Serilog (console, file, request logging) |
| Auth | DedgeAuth SSO (JWT tokens via DedgeAuth.Client library) |
| Web UI | HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript (no Node/npm) |

## Data Flow

```
Log Sources → Import Service → ILogRepository → PostgreSQL
Web UI → REST API → ILogRepository → PostgreSQL
```

## Database migrations

- **Auto-migrate on startup**: Web API and Import Service call `MigrateAsync()` so any pending EF Core migrations are applied automatically; no manual SQL for schema updates.
- **Migrations live in** `GenericLogHandler.Data/Migrations`. Generated for PostgreSQL (Npgsql); design-time factory in Data project uses repo-root `appsettings.json` or env for connection.
- **Adding a new migration** (after changing `LoggingDbContext` or Core entities):  
  `dotnet ef migrations add <MigrationName> --project src/GenericLogHandler.Data --startup-project src/GenericLogHandler.ImportService`  
  Deploy; on next start the app will apply the new migration.
- **One-time reset to latest model** (PostgreSQL): call `POST /api/maintenance/recreate-schema` or run `DatabaseSchemas/PostgreSQL_RecreateTables.sql` then start the app (Migrate will recreate tables).

## Key Interfaces

- `ILogRepository`: All persistence (search, add, delete)
- `ILogImporter`: All ingestion (file, database, eventlog)
- `LogEntry`: Core log record model with business identifiers
- `ImportConfiguration`: JSON-based config for sources, retention, alerts
